text: Tuck away in a corner of the neighborhood, this place forms a community. It's great for the older folks who stays here as it's easy for them to buy daily necessity. The price here is fairly good, reasonable and easy to navigate. Food wise that are good choice of Chinese and Thai cuisine which is definitely a plus. People here speaks many different languages so it's helpful

Affordable & nice fishball & BCM noodle breakfast @ Botak BCM! They also start selling Nonya and Teochew kueh + Mee Hoon Kueh. Western food also quite nice!
Got a new wanton mee + Lor Mee stall started on end sept, taste better than the old one and not much queue.
